(926, '9781430260080', 'Expert PHP and MySQL', 'Application Design and Development', 'Expert PHP and MySQL takes you beyond learning syntax to showing you how to apply proven software development methods to building commerce-grade PHP and MySQL projects that will stand the test of time and reliably deliver on customer needs. Developers of real-world applications face numerous problems that seem trivial on the surface, but really do take some skill to get right. Error handling is about more than just the mechanics in the PHP syntax, but also about handling MySQL errors, logging those errors, and about hiding information about application internals that error messages sometimes can expose. Meet these challenges and more head-on! Author Marc Rochkind shows how to begin a project right, with a clear contract and set of written requirements. You’ll learn about project organization, setting up a solid development environment, connecting with client personnel. Database design is essential, and Expert PHP and MySQL has you covered with guidance on creating a sound model and database, and on pushing functionality into the database as appropriate; not everything should be done in PHP. Error handling is covered at both the PHP and MySQL levels. Application structure is covered. Guidance is provided on reporting. And finally there is conversion. In Expert PHP and MySQL you’ll explore the following: The popular and widely used combination of PHP and MySQL Commercial-grade application of language and database features Human factors such as planning and organization Organizing a project to meet requirements and satisfy the customer Structuring an application for efficient development and future modification Coding PHP for productivity, reliability, security Generating online, downloadable, and printed reports Converting existing data to the new application What you’ll learn Organize a project to meet requirements and satisfy the customer. Structure an application for efficient development and future modification. Design a database to model the business and support the application. Code PHP for productivity, reliability, security. Generate online, downloadable, and printed reports. Convert existing data to the new application. Who this book is for Expert PHP and MySQL is aimed at programmers competent in PHP and MySQL. Readers should know the mechanics of the language and the database, and have a desire to learn to build commercial systems that will stand the test of time and reliably deliver on customer needs. Table of Contents Project Organization Requirements Platforms and Tools The Database Application Structure Security, Forms, and Error Handling Reports and Other Outputs Data Conversion', '2013-08-20', 340, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=JXaSAAAAQBAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=JXaSAAAAQBAJ&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 53, '10.70', 1),
(927, '1852337478', 'PHP and MySQL Manual', 'Simple, Yet Powerful Web Programming', 'This comprehensive manual covers the basic core of the language, with lots of practical examples of some of the more recent and useful features available in version 5.0. MySQL database creation and development is also covered, as it is the developer database most commonly used alongside PHP. It will be an invaluable book for professionals wanting to use PHP to develop their own dynamic web pages.', '2015-10-16', 589, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=qPrWL98_RDQC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=qPrWL98_RDQC&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 87, '13.90', 1),
(928, '1588800539', 'PHP Black Book', NULL, '"The PHP Black Book" is a complete and indispensable reference to the PHP open source scripting language version 4. This cross-platform book covers the language syntax, standard library, and integration with various databases including open source databases such as PostreSQL and MySQL.', '2015-10-16', 845, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=waBQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=waBQAAAAMAAJ&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 247, '32.40', 1),
(929, '1592004946', 'PHP 5/MySQL Programming for the Absolute Beginner', NULL, 'Annotation - Presents the topic in an easy-to-follow format while still relating it to real-world situations- Written by an experienced author and educator, the tone of the book is friendly and non-threatening, but still authoritative- All necessary software is supplied; no other purchase will be necessary for reader.', '2015-10-16', 439, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=hrLWz0XzpWkC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=hrLWz0XzpWkC&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 62, '15.30', 1),
(930, '0764549553', 'PHP Bible', NULL, '* Covers why users need PHP, how to get started, how to add PHP to HTML, and how to connect HTML Web pages to MySQL or Oracle databases. * Authors have extensive experience using PHP and provide case studies of how and where to use PHP. * Covers advanced topics, such as HTTP, cookies, Web services, redirection, building graphics, and sessions.', '2002-10-03', 1032, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=UHHO7HRtL4YC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=UHHO7HRtL4YC&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 233, '24.40', 1),
(931, '0072133716', 'PHP 4', 'A Beginner\'s Guide', 'A tutorial to the open-source HTML-embedded scripting language offers practical projects reviewing PHP scripts, HTML forms, numbers, scalar values, variable types, conditional statments, functions, arrays, and cookies.', '2015-10-16', 567, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=NJLy3VTwmBUC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=NJLy3VTwmBUC&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 13, '21.00', 1),
(932, '013147149X', 'PHP 5 Power Programming', NULL, 'Written by the authors of the actual PHP code! The authoritative developer\'s guide to mastering advanced PHP 5 techniques.', '2015-10-16', 689, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=oJ9QAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=oJ9QAAAAMAAJ&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 224, '26.80', 1),
(933, '2844275915', 'PHP et MySQL pour les nuls', NULL, 'Avec PHP et MySQL pour les Nuls, plus besoin d\'être un as de la programmation pour développer des sites Web dynamiques et interactifs. Avec ce livre, vous apprendrez à manipuler tous les outils de gestion de sessions, manipuler les coockies, gérer le code XML et JavaScript, mettre en place des systèmes de sécurité, et bien d\'autres choses encore.', '2015-10-16', 379, NULL, 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=pZw2HAAACAAJ&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 291, '15.80', 2),
(934, '1931841322', 'PHP/MySQL Programming for the Absolute Beginner', NULL, 'This guide teaches Perl and provides the readers with the fundamental programming concepts they need to grasp in order to learn any new computer language.', '2015-10-16', 414, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=PUoAONZHRYcC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=PUoAONZHRYcC&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 62, '43.70', 1),
(935, '0957921853', 'The PHP Anthology', 'Foundations', 'A compilation of best practice solutions to common Web Development problems in PHP, focusing on the achievement of practical goals by applying well-structured, object orientated software design principles. Volume 1 covers the foundations of PHP including writing portable and reusable code, storing and extracting data from files, manipulating text, working with email and error handling. In addition to being an excellent reference with over 60 customizable solutions, the book acts as an excellent primer for Object Orientated Programming. PHP 5 has now been released and has been given significant OOP features, which are a must-learn for PHP Developers. All code in the book is backwards compatible with earlier versions of PHP.', '2015-10-16', 376, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=7Z1QAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=7Z1QAAAAMAAJ&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 292, '16.20', 1),
(936, 'UOM:39015050117129', 'Professional PHP Programming', NULL, 'PHP is a new technology that is growing fast. It is the open-source that is the next step beyond CGI and is a powerful, evolving alternative to Active Server Pages and Java servlets. Developers who need to build database-driven Web-architecture applications will be pleased with Professional PHP Programming.', '1999-01-01', 909, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=c6hQAAAAMAAJ&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=c6hQAAAAMAAJ&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 53, '44.70', 1),
(937, '9781590597071', 'Beginning Google Maps Applications with PHP and Ajax', 'From Novice to Professional', 'Presents a guide to Google Maps API, demonstrating such tasks as plotting large data sets, creating map overlays, geocoding sets of addresses, and building a geocoder.', '2006-08-22', 358, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=GNMCdlkKU3sC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=GNMCdlkKU3sC&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 24, '20.10', 1),
(938, '1931841349', 'PHP Essentials', NULL, 'Write dynamically generated pages with ease using PHP! Dive into the new edition of this popular guide to PHP. With a true focus on the essentials, this book gives you the solid foundation in PHP programming you\'re looking for. And you don\'t have to be a computer scientist or programmer to learn from it! The simple, learn-by-example format of "PHP Essentials" will allow you to quickly use the power of PHP to develop successful, dynamic Web sites.', '2015-10-16', 326, 'http://books.google.fr/books/content?id=2rzQq8T8beMC&printsec=frontcover&img=1&zoom=1&source=gbs_api', 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=2rzQq8T8beMC&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 293, '11.30', 1),
(939, '2212123698', 'PHP 5 avancé', NULL, 'PHP 5 est plus que jamais la plate-forme incontournable pour le développement d\'applications web professionnelles : programmation objet, services web, couche d\'abstraction de base de données native PDO, simplification des développements XML avec SimpleXML, refonte du moteur sous-jacent pour d\'importants gains de performances... Une bible magistrale avec de nombreux cas pratiques et retours d\'expérience S\'appuyant sur de nombreux retours d\'expérience et cas pratiques, ce livre aidera le développeur à évoluer avec aisance dans le riche univers de PHP 5 et lui donnera toutes les clés pour en maîtriser les subtilités: bonnes pratiques de conception de sites et d\'applications web, frameworks, cookies et sessions, programmation objet, utilisation de XML et SimpleXML, services web, intégration aux bases de données en passant par MySOL 4 et 5, PostgreSQL, PHP Data Object, stratégies d\'optimisation et de sécurité, gestion des images et des caches.... L\'ouvrage consacre un chapitre entier à la migration de PHP 4 vers PHP 5, obligatoire avec l\'arrêt annoncé du support de PHP 4.', '2015-10-16', 843, NULL, 'http://books.google.fr/books?id=VR6jPQAACAAJ&dq=PHP&as_pt=BOOKS&hl=&source=gbs_api', 8, '41.10', 2);
